(42, 17, 20, 42, 19, 11, 11, NULL, 'Expectation of the Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the nature of the kingdom of God. In Luke 17:20, it is stated that the kingdom does not come with observation, while in Luke 19:11, there is an expectation that it should immediately appear.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 20, 44, 1, 6, 7, 'the kingdom of God cometh not with observation', 'Kingdom of God Timing', 'Both passages emphasize the timing of the kingdom of God. In Luke, Jesus states that the kingdom does not come with observation, while in Acts, he indicates that knowledge of its timing is reserved for the Father.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 20, 38, 4, 6, 6, 'kingdom of God cometh not with observation', 'Connection of Divine Power', 'Both passages emphasize that the kingdom of God operates not through human strength or observation but by the Spirit of God. This connection highlights the divine nature of God''s work in establishing His kingdom.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 21, 40, 12, 28, 28, 'kingdom of God', 'Kingdom of God Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the presence of the kingdom of God. Luke 17:21 suggests it is internal, while Matthew 12:28 indicates its arrival through Jesus'' actions.', 'theme', 0.524, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 21, 45, 14, 17, 17, 'the kingdom of God is within you', 'Connection of the Kingdom of God', 'This connection highlights the nature of the kingdom of God as an internal reality rather than an external one. Both passages emphasize that the kingdom involves spiritual qualities such as righteousness, peace, and joy.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 21, 41, 13, 21, 21, 'Lo here! or, lo there!', 'Kingdom of God and Christ''s Presence', 'This connection highlights the theme of the elusive nature of the kingdom of God and Christ''s presence. Both passages caution against seeking the kingdom or Christ in specific locations, emphasizing an internal or spiritual understanding.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 21, 51, 1, 27, 27, 'the kingdom of God is within you', 'Connection of Inner Kingdom and Christ', 'This connection highlights the theme of the divine presence within believers. Both passages emphasize the idea of the kingdom of God and Christ residing within individuals, suggesting an internal spiritual reality.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 21, 42, 10, 9, 11, 'the kingdom of God is within you', 'Connection of the Kingdom of God', 'Both passages emphasize the proximity and internal nature of the kingdom of God. Luke 17:21 states that ''the kingdom of God is within you,'' while Luke 10:9-11 declares that ''the kingdom of God is come nigh unto you.''', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
