(42, 17, 21, 42, 17, 23, 23, 'kingdom of God is within you', 'Connection of Kingdom and Following', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking the kingdom of God. Both passages emphasize the idea of not being misled by external claims about the kingdom''s location.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 22, 40, 9, 15, 15, 'the days will come', 'Connection of Mourning and Absence', 'Both passages emphasize a future time of longing and absence. In Luke, the disciples will desire to see the Son of man, while in Matthew, the bridegroom''s absence leads to mourning. This connection highlights the theme of yearning for the presence of Christ.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 22, 42, 5, 35, 35, 'the days will come', 'Connection of Future Longing', 'Both passages emphasize a future longing for the presence of the Son of Man or the bridegroom. They highlight a time when followers will experience absence and desire for their leader.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 22, 41, 2, 20, 20, 'the days will come', 'Days of the Son of Man', 'Both passages emphasize a future time when the presence of the Son of Man or bridegroom will be absent, leading to a longing or fasting. This connection highlights the anticipation of a significant change in the disciples'' experience.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 22, 43, 7, 33, 36, NULL, 'Seeking and Not Finding Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of seeking Jesus and not being able to find him. In Luke, the disciples will desire to see the days of the Son of man, while in John, Jesus states that they will seek him and shall not find him.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 22, 43, 8, 21, 24, NULL, 'Desire and Seeking in Context', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking Jesus and the consequences of failing to find him. Both passages emphasize a longing for the presence of the Son of Man and the dire implications of not believing in him.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 22, 42, 13, 35, 35, NULL, 'Desolation and Longing for Christ', 'Both passages emphasize a sense of longing for the presence of the Son of Man. In Luke 17:22, the disciples desire to see Him, while in Luke 13:35, the desolation of the house indicates a separation from Him until a future acknowledgment.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 23, 42, 21, 8, 8, NULL, 'Warnings Against Deception', 'Both passages emphasize the need to avoid being misled by false claims of Christ''s presence. They caution followers not to pursue those who assert they have found the Messiah, highlighting the theme of vigilance against deception.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
