(42, 17, 24, 40, 24, 27, 27, 'lightning, that lighteneth out of the one part under heaven', 'Connection of Lightning Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of lightning to describe the coming of the Son of man. This connection highlights the suddenness and visibility of his arrival, as lightning is seen across vast distances.', 'parallel', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
