(42, 17, 24, 38, 9, 14, 14, 'lightning', 'Connection of Lightning Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the imagery of lightning as a sign of divine presence and action. In Luke, the Son of Man''s revelation is likened to lightning, while Zechariah describes the Lord''s arrow going forth as lightning, suggesting a powerful and unmistakable manifestation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 17, 24, 39, 3, 1, 2, NULL, 'Connection of Divine Arrival', 'Both passages emphasize the sudden arrival of the Lord. Luke describes the Son of Man''s coming with a striking image, while Malachi speaks of the Lord coming to His temple unexpectedly. This connection highlights the theme of divine presence and urgency in both texts.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
